msg: Accidentally used WeakReference in docs when I mean SoftReference
Code was not setting "last used" time on return to the pool, tests were passing because of speed (most the time).  Fixed test so false positive is not possible.
GC'ed instances showing up as "collected" in a pop() or pool sweep were not causing a release() on the "instance" Semaphore.
No "stop" method caused tests to build up old pools being continuously sweeped.  Added start/stop, to Pool and call it from tests and StatelessInstanceManager.

Some maxAge related tests would occasionally fail because maxage might be reached on a push() in the test case thread rather than just via the pool sweeping thread.  Fixed Pool to call Supplier.discard() in the "push" thread if something is rejected from the pool.
